# Visual Design System

You are building a **modern, professional SaaS product**. Every screen must feel like it belongs to the same cohesive product. When in doubt, lean toward **clean restraint over decoration**. Clarity and calm confidence are the aesthetic goals.

Read this file completely before touching any UI. Every rule here overrides personal judgment.

---

## 1 — DESIGN PHILOSOPHY

**Core principle:** Reduce cognitive load. Every pixel must earn its place.

The target aesthetic is **refined utility** — the visual language of tools people trust with important work. Think Linear, Vercel, Raycast, Notion. Not playful. Not corporate. Not flashy. Calm, fast, purposeful.

**Four non-negotiables:**
1. **Consistency** — identical components look identical everywhere. No one-off tweaks.
2. **Hierarchy** — one dominant element per screen, then supporting, then metadata.
3. **Whitespace** — negative space is not empty. It is structure.
4. **Feedback** — every interaction has a visible, immediate response.

---

## 2 — COLOR SYSTEM

### Palette definition

Define these as CSS custom properties on `:root`. Use **only** these values throughout the product. No exceptions.

```css
:root {
  /* --- Neutrals (backbone of every screen) --- */
  --color-bg:          #0f0f11;   /* page background */
  --color-surface:     #18181b;   /* cards, panels, dialogs */
  --color-surface-2:   #1f1f23;   /* nested surfaces, hover */
  --color-surface-3:   #27272c;   /* inputs, tags, subtle fills */
  --color-border:      #2e2e35;   /* all dividers and outlines */
  --color-border-focus:#52525e;   /* focused inputs */

  /* --- Text --- */
  --color-text-primary:   #f4f4f5;  /* headings, critical labels */
  --color-text-secondary: #a1a1aa;  /* body copy, descriptions */
  --color-text-tertiary:  #71717a;  /* placeholders, captions */
  --color-text-disabled:  #3f3f46;  /* disabled state labels */
  --color-text-inverse:   #09090b;  /* text on light/accent backgrounds */

  /* --- Brand accent (use sparingly — CTAs, active state, links) --- */
  --color-accent:         #6366f1;  /* indigo-500 */
  --color-accent-hover:   #4f46e5;  /* indigo-600 */
  --color-accent-muted:   rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.12);
  --color-accent-ring:    rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.35);

  /* --- Semantic states --- */
  --color-success:        #22c55e;
  --color-success-muted:  rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.10);
  --color-warning:        #f59e0b;
  --color-warning-muted:  rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.10);
  --color-error:          #ef4444;
  --color-error-muted:    rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.10);
  --color-info:           #3b82f6;
  --color-info-muted:     rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.10);
}
```

### Light mode overrides

If the product supports light mode, override only these tokens — component code never changes:

```css
[data-theme="light"] {
  --color-bg:              #ffffff;
  --color-surface:         #fafafa;
  --color-surface-2:       #f4f4f5;
  --color-surface-3:       #e4e4e7;
  --color-border:          #e4e4e7;
  --color-border-focus:    #a1a1aa;
  --color-text-primary:    #09090b;
  --color-text-secondary:  #52525e;
  --color-text-tertiary:   #a1a1aa;
  --color-text-disabled:   #d4d4d8;
  --color-text-inverse:    #f4f4f5;
}
```

### Color usage rules

| Use case | Token |
|---|---|
| Page background | `--color-bg` |
| Card / panel background | `--color-surface` |
| Nested element within card | `--color-surface-2` |
| Input background | `--color-surface-3` |
| All borders and dividers | `--color-border` |
| All body text | `--color-text-secondary` |
| Headings, critical labels | `--color-text-primary` |
| Placeholder, caption | `--color-text-tertiary` |
| Primary button, active link, badge | `--color-accent` |
| Hover on accent | `--color-accent-hover` |
| Subtle accent background | `--color-accent-muted` |

**Accent usage limit:** No more than **2–3 accent-colored elements visible at once**. If every button is accent-colored, nothing stands out.

**Never use:**
- Raw hex values anywhere in components
- `opacity` to create color variants — use dedicated tokens
- `white` or `black` literals — use text/bg tokens
- More than one accent hue per screen (no rainbow palettes)

