## 3 — TYPOGRAPHY

### Font stack

```css
:root {
  --font-sans:  'Geist', 'Inter', ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-mono:  'Geist Mono', 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
}
```

Load via `@font-face` or CDN. Geist is preferred (Vercel open source). Fall back to Inter. Never fall back to Arial, Helvetica, or system default without specifying Inter first.

### Type scale

```css
:root {
  --text-xs:   0.6875rem;  /* 11px — labels, badges, legal */
  --text-sm:   0.8125rem;  /* 13px — secondary UI, captions */
  --text-base: 0.9375rem;  /* 15px — body copy, inputs */
  --text-md:   1.0625rem;  /* 17px — emphasized body */
  --text-lg:   1.25rem;    /* 20px — card titles, section labels */
  --text-xl:   1.5rem;     /* 24px — page subtitles */
  --text-2xl:  1.875rem;   /* 30px — page titles */
  --text-3xl:  2.25rem;    /* 36px — hero headlines */
  --text-4xl:  3rem;       /* 48px — marketing / splash */

  --leading-tight:  1.2;
  --leading-snug:   1.375;
  --leading-normal: 1.5;
  --leading-relaxed:1.625;

  --tracking-tight: -0.02em;
  --tracking-normal: 0em;
  --tracking-wide:  0.04em;
  --tracking-widest:0.1em;
}
```

### Typography rules

**Headings:**
- `font-weight: 600` for H1–H3. `font-weight: 500` for H4–H6.
- Letter spacing: `--tracking-tight` on anything `--text-xl` and above.
- Color: `--color-text-primary`.
- Line height: `--leading-tight` for display, `--leading-snug` for headers.

**Body:**
- `font-weight: 400` for prose. `font-weight: 500` for emphasized labels.
- Color: `--color-text-secondary`. Reserve `--color-text-primary` for truly critical text.
- Line height: `--leading-normal` or `--leading-relaxed` for paragraph text.

**Labels / metadata:**
- `font-weight: 500`, `--text-xs` or `--text-sm`, `--tracking-wide`, `text-transform: uppercase` only for category labels and section dividers. Not for regular UI labels.

**Code and monospace:**
- Always `--font-mono`. Never fake code with sans-serif.
- Background: `--color-surface-3`. Padding: `2px 6px`. Border-radius: `--radius-sm`.

**Anti-patterns to reject:**
- Never `font-weight: 700` in UI (it's for marketing, not product)
- Never mix more than 2 font weights per component
- Never set explicit `font-size` in `px` — always use scale tokens
- Never center-align body text blocks over 2 lines

---

## 4 — SPACING SYSTEM

All spacing is built on a **4px base unit**. Every margin, padding, and gap must be a multiple of 4.

```css
:root {
  --space-0:   0px;
  --space-1:   4px;
  --space-2:   8px;
  --space-3:   12px;
  --space-4:   16px;
  --space-5:   20px;
  --space-6:   24px;
  --space-8:   32px;
  --space-10:  40px;
  --space-12:  48px;
  --space-16:  64px;
  --space-20:  80px;
  --space-24:  96px;
  --space-32:  128px;
}
```

### Spacing conventions

| Context | Token |
|---|---|
| Inside a button | `--space-2` top/bottom, `--space-4` left/right |
| Inside a card | `--space-6` |
| Between form fields | `--space-4` |
| Section vertical padding | `--space-12` or `--space-16` |
| Page horizontal padding | `--space-6` (mobile), `--space-8` (tablet), `--space-12` (desktop) |
| Between related elements (icon + label) | `--space-2` |
| Between unrelated sections | `--space-8` minimum |
| Inline badge/tag padding | `--space-1` top/bottom, `--space-2` left/right |

**Never use arbitrary values** like `padding: 18px` or `gap: 7px`. If a value doesn't exist in the scale, use the nearest token.

---

## 5 — BORDER RADIUS

```css
:root {
  --radius-none: 0px;
  --radius-sm:   4px;   /* tags, code, subtle elements */
  --radius-md:   8px;   /* buttons, inputs, small cards */
  --radius-lg:   12px;  /* cards, panels, modals */
  --radius-xl:   16px;  /* large cards, feature blocks */
  --radius-2xl:  24px;  /* sheet modals, bottom drawers */
  --radius-full: 9999px; /* pills, avatars, toggle tracks */
}
```

**Usage rules:**
- Buttons: `--radius-md`
- Inputs: `--radius-md`
- Cards and panels: `--radius-lg`
- Tooltips: `--radius-md`
- Avatars: `--radius-full`
- Modal dialogs: `--radius-xl`
- Inline code: `--radius-sm`
- Never mix radius sizes within the same card (all corners must match)

---

## 6 — ELEVATION & SHADOWS

Shadows convey layer depth, not decoration. Use the minimum shadow needed to establish hierarchy.

```css
:root {
  --shadow-none:  none;
  --shadow-xs:    0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  --shadow-sm:    0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
  --shadow-md:    0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  --shadow-lg:    0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.45);
  --shadow-xl:    0 16px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  --shadow-focus: 0 0 0 3px var(--color-accent-ring);
  --shadow-focus-error: 0 0 0 3px rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.35);
}
```

**Layer model (dark theme):**

| Layer | Shadow |
|---|---|
| Flat element on bg | `--shadow-none` — use border instead |
| Card / panel | `--shadow-sm` + `1px solid var(--color-border)` |
| Dropdown / popover | `--shadow-md` |
| Modal / dialog | `--shadow-lg` |
| Tooltip | `--shadow-sm` |
| Focused input | `--shadow-focus` (replace outline) |

**Rule:** In dark UI, borders are more important than shadows for separation. Use `border: 1px solid var(--color-border)` as primary separation; add shadow only when an element must float above the page.

