## 10 — MOTION

All transitions use these timing functions:

```css
:root {
  --ease-out:     cubic-bezier(0.0, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0);  /* elements entering */
  --ease-in:      cubic-bezier(0.4, 0.0, 1.0, 1.0);  /* elements leaving */
  --ease-in-out:  cubic-bezier(0.4, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0);  /* elements moving */
  --ease-spring:  cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1.0); /* bouncy reveals */
}
```

### Duration scale

```css
:root {
  --duration-instant: 75ms;
  --duration-fast:   150ms;
  --duration-normal: 200ms;
  --duration-slow:   300ms;
  --duration-slower: 400ms;
}
```

### Motion rules

| Interaction | Duration | Easing |
|---|---|---|
| Button hover/press | `--duration-fast` | `--ease-in-out` |
| Input focus ring | `--duration-fast` | `--ease-out` |
| Dropdown open | `--duration-normal` | `--ease-out` |
| Dropdown close | `--duration-fast` | `--ease-in` |
| Modal enter | `--duration-slow` | `--ease-spring` |
| Modal exit | `--duration-normal` | `--ease-in` |
| Page content enter | `--duration-slow` | `--ease-out` |
| Skeleton → content crossfade | `--duration-normal` | `--ease-in-out` |
| Toast enter | `--duration-normal` | `--ease-spring` |
| Toast exit | `--duration-fast` | `--ease-in` |

**Enter animation (standard):**
```css
@keyframes fadeInUp {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px); }
  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
.animate-enter {
  animation: fadeInUp var(--duration-slow) var(--ease-out) both;
}
```

**Stagger pattern (lists, cards grids):**
```tsx
{items.map((item, i) => (
  <div
    key={item.id}
    style={{ animationDelay: `${i * 50}ms` }}
    className="animate-enter"
  />
))}
```

**Never animate:** `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom`. Only `transform` and `opacity`.

**Reduced motion:**
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

