## 13 — WRITING & CONTENT

Good design requires good copy. The agent must follow these standards for all UI text it generates.

**Labels and headings:**
- Sentence case for everything: "Account settings" not "Account Settings"
- No trailing periods on labels, buttons, headings
- Buttons are verbs: "Save changes", "Create invoice", "Delete account" — not "Save", "Create", "Delete" (too terse) and not "Click here to save" (too verbose)

**Empty states:** Specific, not generic.
- ✅ "No invoices yet — create your first one to get started"
- ❌ "No data available"

**Error messages:** Human and actionable.
- ✅ "We couldn't load your invoices. Check your connection and try again."
- ❌ "Error: 500 Internal Server Error"

**Loading states:** Silent — no "Loading…" text unless operation takes > 3 seconds. Use skeleton UI.

